  "text": "## HTTP Request Header Injection Validation in Envoy\n\nEnvoy implements comprehensive header validation and sanitization across multiple layers to prevent HTTP request header injection attacks:\n\n### Core Header Validation (source/common/http/)\n\n**header_utility.cc/h**: Contains fundamental header validation functions:\n- `headerNameIsValid()` - Validates header names per RFC 7230, checking for valid token characters\n- `headerValueIsValid()` - Validates header values, disallowing control characters and invalid sequences\n- `requestHeadersValid()` - Comprehensive validation checking authority, method, and scheme validity\n- `checkValidRequestHeaders()` - Validates all header keys and values to prevent embedded NULLs and newlines\n- `checkRequiredRequestHeaders()` - Ensures required headers (:method, :path, :authority) are present\n- `checkHeaderNameForUnderscores()` - Prevents headers with underscores which may be confused with hyphens\n- `isEnvoyInternalRequest()` - Identifies and manages internal request markers\n- `validateContentLength()` - Validates Content-Length header to prevent request smuggling\n\n**utility.cc/h**: Contains `Utility::sanitizeConnectionHeader()` function that:\n- Prevents header injection via the Connection header nomination mechanism\n- Rejects attempts to nominate X-Forwarded-* headers or pseudo-headers (starting with ':')\n- Limits nominated headers to 10 maximum to prevent DoS\n- Sanitizes the TE header to only allow 'trailers' value\n- Validates TE header size doesn't exceed 256 bytes\n- Enforces HTTP/2 semantics for Connection header handling\n\n### Connection Manager Processing (source/common/http/conn_manager_*)\n\n**conn_manager_impl.cc/h**: Request header processing pipeline:\n- `ConnectionManagerImpl::ActiveStream::decodeHeaders()` - Entry point for incoming request headers\n- `ConnectionManagerImpl::ActiveStream::validateHeaders()` - Triggers header validator on all incoming requests\n- Integrates with `ServerHeaderValidator` to validate and transform headers\n- Handles header validation errors with appropriate HTTP 400 responses\n- Tracks validation metrics and enforces protocol-specific behavior\n\n**conn_manager_utility.cc/h**: Header mutation and sanitization:\n- `mutateRequestHeaders()` - Core function that:\n  - Removes proxy-related headers via `removeConnection()`, `removeUpgrade()`, `removeProxyConnection()`\n  - Calls `sanitizeTEHeader()` to prevent TE-based header attacks\n  - Removes internal Envoy markers: `removeEnvoyInternalRequest()`\n  - Sanitizes the Referer header by validating it against `isValidRefererValue()`\n  - Handles X-Forwarded-* headers based on trust configuration\n\n- `cleanInternalHeaders()` - Strips security-sensitive internal headers:\n  - From edge requests (to prevent client injection): x-envoy-decorator-operation, x-envoy-downstream-service-cluster, x-envoy-downstream-service-node, x-envoy-original-path\n  - From all external requests: x-envoy-retriable-status-codes, x-envoy-retriable-header-names, x-envoy-retry-on, x-envoy-max-retries, x-envoy-upstream-request-timeout-ms, x-envoy-upstream-request-per-try-timeout-ms, x-envoy-force-trace, and others\n\n- `sanitizeTEHeader()` - Runtime-configurable TE header sanitization:\n  - Extracts and validates TE header values\n  - Only allows 'trailers' value, removes all others\n  - Removes TE header if it doesn't contain 'trailers'\n\n### Protocol-Specific Header Validators (source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/)\n\n**header_validator.cc/h** - Base validation class:\n- `validateMethodHeader()` - Validates HTTP method against RFC standards with optional strict method registry\n- `validateSchemeHeader()` - Restricts to 'http' and 'https' schemes\n- `validateStatusHeader()` - Ensures status codes are 100-999 range\n- `validateGenericHeaderName()` - Enforces token syntax per RFC 9110\n- `validateContentLengthHeader()` - Prevents request smuggling via Content-Length inconsistencies\n- `sanitizeHeadersWithUnderscores()` - Drops or rejects headers containing underscores based on configuration (DROP_HEADER or REJECT_REQUEST actions)\n- `sanitizePathWithFragment()` - Removes URI fragments from paths\n- `sanitizeEncodedSlashes()` - Handles percent-encoded slashes to prevent path traversal\n\n**http1_header_validator.cc/h** - HTTP/1.1 specific:\n- `validateRequestHeaderEntry()` - Validates HTTP/1.1 headers with stricter character set requirements\n- `validateTransferEncodingHeader()` - Validates chunked encoding headers\n- `validatePathHeaderWithAdditionalCharacters()` - Optional relaxed path validation mode\n\n**http2_header_validator.cc/h** - HTTP/2 specific:\n- `validateRequestHeaderEntry()` - Validates pseudo-headers (:method, :authority, :scheme, :path, :protocol)\n- `validateAuthorityHeader()` - Validates authority header with HTTP/2 specific rules\n- `validateTEHeader()` - HTTP/2 restricts TE to 'trailers' only\n- `validateContentLengthHeader()` - Additional validation for HTTP/2 Content-Length constraints\n- Prevents Connection header which is forbidden in HTTP/2\n\n### HTTP/1 Codec Validation (source/common/http/http1/)\n\n**codec_impl.cc/h** - Low-level HTTP/1 parsing:\n- Calls `Utility::sanitizeConnectionHeader()` to validate Connection header before request processing\n- Returns 400 Bad Request if Connection header validation fails\n- Integrates with balsa_parser for RFC-compliant header name/value parsing\n\n### JWT Filter Header Sanitization (source/extensions/filters/http/jwt_authn/)\n\n**extractor.cc/h** - JWT-specific header handling:\n- `ExtractorImpl::sanitizeHeaders()` - Removes JWT tokens after extraction from specified headers\n- Prevents JWT tokens from being forwarded upstream in sensitive header combinations\n- Maintains list of headers to sanitize based on configured JWT locations\n\n### Header Map Implementation (source/common/http/header_map_impl.*)\n\n**headers.h** - Defines all standard header constants and removal methods for security-sensitive headers:\n- Provides typed accessors like `removeEnvoyInternalRequest()`, `removeEnvoyDecoratorOperation()`, `removeEnvoyDownstreamServiceCluster()`, etc.\n- Ensures header removal is type-safe and prevents accidental partial removal\n- Centralizes header name definitions to prevent typos\n\n### Key Security Mechanisms\n\n1. **Header Injection Prevention**:\n   - Connection header nomination attack prevention via `sanitizeConnectionHeader()`\n   - Limits connections header values to 10 nominated headers maximum\n   - Prevents X-Forwarded-* and pseudo-header nomination\n   - TE header size limits (max 256 bytes)\n\n2. **Internal Header Stripping**:\n   - `cleanInternalHeaders()` removes all x-envoy-* internal headers from edge requests\n   - Prevents clients from forging internal routing decisions\n   - Enforces trust boundaries between edge and internal proxies\n\n3. **Header Validation**:\n   - Validates header names and values per RFC standards\n   - Rejects headers with embedded NULLs, newlines, and invalid control characters\n   - Underscore detection and rejection in header names\n   - HTTP/2 pseudo-header validation\n   - Content-Length validation to prevent request smuggling\n\n4. **Runtime Configuration**:\n   - Headers with underscores can be ALLOW, DROP_HEADER, or REJECT_REQUEST\n   - TE header sanitization can be disabled via runtime features\n   - Path normalization and validation configurable\n   - Header validation strictness adjustable via HeaderValidatorConfig\n\nThese mechanisms work together to ensure that external request headers cannot be crafted to inject commands, break out of intended header semantics, or manipulate internal Envoy routing and processing logic."
